cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of off-grid small-cell base stations, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the power requirements and constraints for mobile terminals and base stations, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new cell association strategy that adapts to fluctuations in base station battery and user power requirements, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the power required to satisfy a received power constraint at each mobile terminal, which could be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry tools to estimate the power consumed to serve other mobile terminals potentially associated to the same base station, which could be related to game theory.
